Plan
- Rotate the vector z − c by 45° about the origin, then translate back by c.

Solution steps
- z = 2 + √2 − (3 + 3√2)i, c = 2 − 3i.
- z − c = (2 + √2 − 2) + (−(3 + 3√2) + 3)i = √2 − 3√2 i = √2(1 − 3i).
